ch.epfl.lasec.evoting
Class Ballot

java.lang.Object
  ch.epfl.lasec.evoting.Ballot

public class Ballot
extends java.lang.Object

class representing a ballot. A ballot is a list of objects to be voted, it is also represented by a unique identifier.

Author:
Sebastien Duc

addVotingElection

public void addVotingElection(java.lang.String subject,
                              java.lang.String[] candidatesFirstName,
                              java.lang.String[] candidatesLastName)
This method adds an election submitted on vote. The ith candidate has its first name in the i_th element of candidatesFirstName and its last name in the i_th element of candidatesLastName. Both String arrays must have the same size.

Parameters:
subject - The subject of election
candidatesFirstName - The list of candidates first name
candidatesLastName - The list of candidates last name
